Education PS Belio Kipsang has revised the school closing dates to avoid disruption of classes during elections.Kipsang, in a directive issued to county education regional coordinators and other officials, said schools will close between July 28 and August 4. However, the opening dates for term three will remain unchanged, Kipsang said.Schools open on August 24 for the third term.Nearly all learning institutions will serve as polling stations while members of staff will be engaged as polling officers during the August 8 polls.Kipsang warned politicians against having partisan political activities within learning institutions. &ldquo;All interactions between political parties and politicians and educational institutions should be structured, formal and documented,&rdquo; he said.